Flask is a lightweight,
flexible Python web framework that build web applications and APIs with minimal setup.
What Flask is made of
At its core, Flask provides:
✔ A web server
✔ Routing (URL → function)
✔ Request/response handling
✔ Template rendering (Jinja2)
✔ Extensions for anything else (ORM, auth, forms, etc.)
A real Flask project structure
Python files (app.py, routes.py, models.py)
HTML templates (index.html, inventory.html)
A working REST API
A working UI page
A working Chart.js  dashboard

############## FLASH STRUCTURE ############


flask_inventory/
│
├── app.py
├── routes.py
├── models.py
├── inventory_data.py
│
└── templates/
    ├── index.html
    ├── inventory.html
    └── chart.html

##############


Home: http://localhost:5000
Search UI: http://localhost:5000/inventory
Chart Dashboard: http://localhost:5000/chart
REST API: http://localhost:5000/api/inventory

